    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like you're being a bit dismissive of the actual math. grants don't always cover everything, and they usually come with their own mountains of red tape. it seems like you're framing the economic risks as just \"pessimism\" while treating the environmental benefits as if they're a guaranteed win for these businesses. can you actually name some of the specific economic downsides that people are worried about without calling them just \"fears\"?",
